The management of Caleb University, Imota, Lagos State has joined millions of Nigerians in rejoicing with the foremost statesman, Chief Edwin Kiagbodo Clark as he turns 95-years-old. Chief Edwin Kiagbodi Clark is the Chancellor of Caleb University, Lagos. The University congratulated the elder statement in a message signed by its Registrar, Mr Mayokun Olumeru -Advertisement- The message read, “We join the rest of the world in celebrating a foremost Nigerian leader, a fearless crusader, a passionate educationist, a University Visitor and Proprietor, a tested and trusted philanthropist, a brilliant legal luminary, the conscience of the Niger Delta, a Patriarch of the Masses, a National Colossus and a respected Global Citizen. “Sir, since coming on board as our Chancellor, Caleb University has benefitted immensely from your wealth of experience. “Indeed, you are a blessing to us! The statement added: “Happy birthday, long life and prosperity, Mr Chancellor, Sir.”